```mermaid
flowchart TD
    RL[Raw Resources<br/>from discovery] --> Filter{Settings Filter}

    Filter -->|enabled non-empty| KeepOnly[Keep only in enabled list]
    Filter -->|disabled non-empty| Exclude[Exclude items in disabled list]
    Filter -->|both empty| All[Keep all]

    KeepOnly --> Output[Filtered Resources]
    Exclude --> Output
    All --> Output

    Output --> Metadata[Preserve PathMetadata<br/>source, origin, path]
    Metadata --> Done[Ready for use]
```

---

**Explanation**:
- For each resource type (extensions, skills, prompts, themes), after discovery, the loader applies settings-based filtering.
- Logic (in `getEnabledResources`):
  - If `enabled` array is non-empty, only resources whose path is in `enabled` are kept.
  - Else if `disabled` array is non-empty, resources in `disabled` are removed.
  - Else all resources are kept.
- Filtering respects `PathMetadata` so we still know origin for reload and diagnostics.
- Filtered resources are then returned by `getExtensions()`, `getSkills()`, etc.
